    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Demo 3 — Contact List Lifecycle (CRUD)\n\nSeeds a contacts table, activates the entries with a valid e-mail, deletes the rest, and reads back the result.\n\nFully **idempotent**: the table is rebuilt on every run — no manual cleanup.\n\n**Expected output:** exactly 2 items, both `STATUS = \"active\"`.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 900,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000001",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -80,
        -460
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Resolve the write schema\n\nNothing is hardcoded: `SELECT COALESCE(CURRENT_SCHEMA, CURRENT_USER)` returns your credential’s *Default Schema*, or falls back to the schema named after your database user.\n\nSet the credential’s Default Schema to redirect all writes.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000002",
      "name": "Sticky Note2",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        270,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Reset the demo table\n\n`CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE` gives every run a clean slate. *Restrict to SELECT Queries* is disabled here for the DDL.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000003",
      "name": "Sticky Note3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        570,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Seed & bulk insert\n\nThe Code node emits 3 items with **UPPERCASE keys** — the Exasol node quotes identifiers, and Exasol stores unquoted names uppercase.\n\n*Insert* auto-maps the items into **one batched INSERT** and returns a single `{ affectedRows: 3 }` item, so each following node runs exactly once.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 560
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000004",
      "name": "Sticky Note4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        870,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Validate & purge\n\n*Update* uses *Map Each Column Below* plus a `LIKE ‘%@example.com’` condition to activate valid contacts, stamping `UPDATED_AT` via an expression.\n\n*Delete* removes what is left in status `new`.\n\nBoth operations **require at least one WHERE condition** — the node refuses to touch a whole table.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 560
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000005",
      "name": "Sticky Note5",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1470,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Verify the result\n\nSelect Rows sorted by `ID` — always 2 active contacts, Ada and Grace.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
      "id": "d3s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000006",
      "name": "Sticky Note6",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2070,
        -160
      ]
    }
  ],
